SESSION LOG
===========
Timestamp : 20260406_232429
User      : Bardock
Request   : I want to scan an old hard drive enclosure for a server. I want to make some changes and print out a few cheap prototype and use them as refrence to finalize the design. Then I want to print a high quality version

APPROVED PLAN
-------------
Step 1: 3D Scanner
Scan the old hard drive enclosure to create a digital 3D model.
Duration: 2h - Booking required: Yes

Step 2: Fusion 360
Import the scanned data, convert to a solid model, and design the necessary modifications for the new enclosure version.
Duration: 8h - Booking required: No

Step 3: Cura
Prepare the modified design for FDM 3D printing by slicing the model and generating G-code for cheap prototypes.
Duration: 1h - Booking required: No

Step 4: FDM 3D Printer
Print several cheap prototypes to evaluate the design, fit, and functionality.
Duration: 12h - Booking required: Yes

Step 5: Calipers
Inspect and measure the prototypes to identify areas for improvement and finalize the design.
Duration: 2h - Booking required: No

Step 6: Fusion 360
Apply final design adjustments to the 3D model based on prototype evaluation.
Duration: 4h - Booking required: No

Step 7: PreForm
Prepare the finalized design for high-quality SLA 3D printing, including orienting the model.
Duration: 1h - Booking required: No

Step 8: SLA 3D Printer
Print the high-quality version of the hard drive enclosure.
Duration: 10h - Booking required: Yes

Step 9: UV Curing Station
Post-cure the SLA printed part to achieve final material properties and strength.
Duration: 3h - Booking required: Yes

Step 10: Calipers
Perform a final quality inspection, including dimensional accuracy, on the high-quality printed enclosure.
Duration: 1h - Booking required: No


